# Golem Module Structure

## Module Naming
- Module files: `mod_name.R` (e.g., [mod_risk.R](mdc:R/mod_risk.R))
- UI function: `mod_name_ui()` (e.g., `mod_risk_ui()`)
- Server function: `mod_name_server()` (e.g., `mod_risk_server()`)
- Use snake_case for module names

## Module Structure
```r
#' module_name UI Function
#' @param id,input,output,session Internal parameters for {shiny}
#' @noRd
mod_name_ui <- function(id) {
  ns <- NS(id)
  tagList(
    # UI elements here
  )
}

#' module_name Server Functions
#' @param id,input,output,session Internal parameters for {shiny}
#' @noRd
mod_name_server <- function(id) {
  moduleServer(id, function(input, output, session) {
    ns <- session$ns
    # Server logic here
  })
}
```

## App Orchestration
- [app_server.R](mdc:R/app_server.R) and [app_ui.R](mdc:R/app_ui.R) should ONLY orchestrate modules
- NO business logic in app_server or app_ui
- Use `mod_name_ui("module_id")` and `mod_name_server("module_id")` to include modules